  sentences:
  - speakerIndex: 1
    fontStyle: 2
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: You opened the chest, and a sound starts playing immediately.
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: If you found this it means you wanted to know the truth. We figured
      we might as well leave a note for someone in the future.
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: 'It was 2040. Humans had ignored climate change and damaged the world
      irreversibly. They had continued to pollute the Earth endlessly. '
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "As the Earth was ravaged, humans began to see the consequences of
      their actions\u2026. Food insecurity, reduced crop yields, increased migration
      and dramatic damage to coastal communities was only the beginning\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: 'Clean drinkable water became more and more scarce. Those years of
      polluting the Earth came back to haunt them. As the water rose it only became
      more polluted as it swallowed entire states on each continent. '
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "The increased global temperatures killed the sea and all the animals
      that called it their home. Humanity's punishment was unfolding on all fronts\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "However, it wasn't lack of drinking water, the death of the sea, or
      increasing temperature that led to war\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: Rather the nations and leaders of the world began blaming one another,
      arguments became less about how to solve the issue and more about who held
      the most blame.
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: Of course there were still people working to fix the climate but the
      world was primed for war.
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "Icebergs were one of the few sources of fresh water still left\u2026.
      Naturally tensions had been increasing over the remaining icebergs and which
      nations would harvest them\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "The world powers used their military dominance to take as much as
      they could for themselves. It wasn't long until people crushed under the weight
      of starvation and burned by the heat of thirst broke\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "Humans have been known to do amazing things and be amazing people\u2026.but
      they have also been known to wear a face of hate, greed, and hubris that disgusted
      even the devil."
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "Wars, genocides, and facism are common for humanity\u2026. So it was
      no surprise when nations started launching nuclear warheads\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "With 14 thousand nuclear weapons in humanity\u2019s arsenal, no one
      was safe. Every major figure in the world was killed. Every major city decimated.
      Entire nations were leveled\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "The nuclear fallout was so saturated that even those that survived
      the blasts couldnt step outside\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "Over the next few years the survivors found each other through chance.
      Only 8 humans had survived\u2026. Each was able to walk outside with no negative
      reactions. It seemed almost as if they were being protected\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: Over the years they were able to slowly build a small society with
      children. As the children were growing the initial survivors met.
  - speakerIndex: 0
    fontStyle: 0
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: "They chose to rewrite history and instill lessons of humility and
      compassion for others and nature\u2026. To prevent society from walking the
      same path that led to their demise\u2026"
  - speakerIndex: 1
    fontStyle: 2
    fontOverride: {fileID: 0}
    sentence: End of message
